## 4. Database Models

### Enums
```
UserRole:      USER | ADMIN
RentalStatus:  ACTIVE | EXPIRED | PAUSED | SUSPENDED
ProviderType:  openai | gemini | anthropic
```

### Plan (core table)
```
price (USD float)               one-time charge
duration_minutes (int)          rental window length
token_cap (int)                 hard token ceiling (pre-calculated per model)
rpm_limit (int)                 requests per minute
drain_rate_multiplier (float)   ‚âà1.0 for all new plans (kept for legacy)
model_id (str, nullable)  ‚òÖ     "gpt-4o-mini" / null = universal plan
duration_label (str, nullable)‚òÖ "1 hour" (display string shown in UI)
is_active (bool)
```

> **Rule:** Create one Plan per `model_id √ó duration_minutes` combination.
> Token cap should already account for the model's cost (see ¬ß7 formula).

### Rental
```
virtual_key (str, unique)       the vk_xxx key delivered to user
status (RentalStatus)
tokens_used, tokens_remaining
requests_made
ip_address                      IP-pinned after first use
started_at, expires_at
cashfree_order_id               payment reference
```

### ProviderKey
```
provider (ProviderType)
api_key (str, hashed at rest)
is_active (bool)
usage_count, last_used_at
```

> `GET /api/active-providers` uses this table to tell the frontend which
> models are currently available to users.

